From Brother Roy Subject RFD This is a RFD on a proposal for a newsgroup which would promote a sharing on the Johannine hours as proposed each month by the monks of the ecumenical community of Taize pronounced te zay in NAME OF PROPOSED NEWSGROUP Unmoderated PURPOSE OF THE GROUP The Taize Community is an international ecumenical community of monks based in Many young adults come there to search for meaning in their life and to deepen their understanding of their faith through a sharing with This newsgroup will allow such a sharing through a monthly Johannine Hour which will be posted at the beginning of each A Johannine hour involves a short commentary on a given Bible passage followed by some questions for Any thoughts that may arise in consequence and that you wish to share with others can be posted We are not interested in theological debate and even less in No expertise is required The idea is to help one another to deepen our understanding of Scripture as it is related to our own life The idea of Johannine hours was born in Taize as a simple response to all those who were trying to assimilate the Bible's message in the midst of their daily Because of work or studies it is often impossible to spend long hours in silence and reflection but everyone can take an hour from time to time to enter a church sit quietly at home or go out for a walk in the There in silence we can meditate on a passage of Scripture to listen to the voice of During the time of silence it is important to concentrate on what we understand and not waste time worrying if in some Biblical expressions we find it difficult to hear the voice of The idea is to communicate to others what we have understood of Christ not burdening them with our own hesitations but rather telling them what has brought us joy what has led us to run the risk of trusting more Perhaps those who read and think about the Johannine Hours in this newsgroup could share their reflections and discoveries with The important thing is the complementarity between two aspects the personal aspect of silent personal reflection and the communal aspect of sharing which through Usenet makes us a part of a worldwide BACKGROUND OF THE TAIZE COMMUNITY The following provides some background information on the life and vocation of the Taize pronounced te zay A PARABLE OF COMMUNION August with Europe in the grip of World War II Brother Roger aged set up home in the almost abandoned village of Taize in Eastern His dream to bring together a monastic community which would live out a parable of community a sign of reconciliation in the midst of the distress of the Centering his life on prayer he used his house to conceal refugees especially Jews fleeing from the Nazi AN INTERNATIONAL AND ECUMENICAL COMMUNITY Taize's founder spent the first two years Others joined him later and at Easter seven brothers committed themselves together to common life and Year by year still others have entered the community each one making a lifelong commitment after several years of Today there are brothers Catholics and from various Protestant backgrounds from over twenty different Some of them are living in small groups in poor neighbourhoods in Asia Africa North and South The brothers accept no donations or gifts for themselves not even family inheritances and the community holds no The brothers earn their living and share with others entirely through their own In Sisters of Saint Andrew an international Catholic community founded years ago came to live in the neighbouring village to share the responsibility of welcoming people in TAIZE AND THE YOUNG THE INTERCONTINENTAL MEETINGS Young adults and less young have been coming to Taize in ever greater numbers since Hundreds of thousands of people from Europe and far beyond have thus been brought together in a common Intercontinental meetings take place each week Sunday to Sunday throughout the year and they include youth from between and countries during any one The meetings give each person the opportunity to explore the roots of their faith and to reflect on how to unite the inner life and human The meetings in summer can have up to participants a Three times every day the brothers and everybody on the hill come together for common prayer in the Church of Reconciliation built in when the village church became too A PILGRIMAGE OF TRUST ON EARTH The community has never wanted to create a movement around Instead people are called to commit themselves in their church at home in their neighbourhood their city or To support them in this Taize has created what it calls a pilgrimage of trust on earth At the end of each year the pilgrimage has a European meeting which brings together tens of thousands of young adults from every part of Europe for several days in a major There have also been meetings in Asia and in the United Every year Brother Roger writes an open letter to the Usually completed during a stay in one of the poor regions of the world these are translated into thirty languages and provide themes for reflexion for the following NOTE Discussion on the creation of this newsgroup will take place in For any further information contact Taize Community TAIZE France